  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Event  
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    CalendarFrame
    CalendarFrame displays an interactive calendar that allows you to input different events for certain dates as well as other features such as exercises or a funny picture.
    CalendarInfo
    Class that contains most of a Calendar's info This class was taken/adapted from https://introcs.cs.princeton.edu/java/21function/Calendar.java.html, credits to princeton as well as https://github.com/dwatring/Memo-Calendar/blob/master/src/CalendarData.java , author dwatring
    CalendarRunner
    Main runner of the Calendar Program
    DateAdapter
    Class that implements MouseListener to add more functionality to it
    DateEvent
    DateEvent is the main type of object stored in the EventList (can store others).
    EventList
    EventList is the object used to hold the events for the calendar, where you are able to add and remove events.
    QuoteReader
    QuoteReader is used to read in which the file of quotes and get a quote for the day.
    RandomNumGenerator
    This follows conventions of a Singleton Number Generator (Design Pattern)
    ReminderEvent
    A reminder event is based off a DateEvent, with changes only in colors
    UrgentEvent
    An urgent event follows guidelines of DateEvent but with a different font color
